Job Description:
The NYC Department of Consumer and Worker Protection (DCWP) protects and enhances the daily economic lives of New Yorkers to create thriving communities. DCWP licenses more than 81,000 businesses in more than 50 industries and enforces key consumer protection, licensing, and workplace laws that apply to countless more. By supporting businesses through equitable enforcement and access to resources and, by helping to resolve complaints, DCWP protects the marketplace from predatory practices and strives to create a culture of compliance. Through its community outreach and the work of its offices of Financial Empowerment and Labor Policy & Standards, DCWP empowers consumers and working families by providing the tools and resources they need to be educated consumers and to achieve financial health and work-life balance. DCWP also conducts research and advocates for public policy that furthers its work to support New York City’s communities. For more information about DCWP and its work, call 311 or visit DCWP at nyc.gov/dca or on its social media sites, Twitter, Facebook, Instagram and YouTube.

The Enforcement Division at DCWP seeks experienced employees to serve in Senior Inspector positions. The Senior Inspectors, reporting to the Borough Manager and upper management will be responsible for performing the duties of Inspector Assignment Level I, and current duties of Assignment level II, the senior inspectors will design and deliver trainings for staff.

Responsibilities include but are not limited to:

• Conducting general vending field enforcement and participating in multi-agency street vendor enforcement actions;

• Working closely with other Divisions in developing checklists through feedback;

• Developing training manuals/documents to support consistency in operations;

• Researching laws, highlighting issues, developing protocols and procedures for inspections;

• Following up on dismissals and developing relevant training to minimize case loss;

• Delivering training in a one on one and group setting as needed;

• Leading test runs and recommending quality control measures for efficiencies;

• Assisting Associate Inspectors by making spot checks of investigations and reviewing reports of Inspectors.

Preferred Skills:
• Strong written and oral communication skills;

• Ability to develop and motivate staff with a team-oriented approach;

• Proficiency in Microsoft Word, Outlook, and Excel;

• Thorough knowledge of technical systems and research techniques;

• Strong written and oral communication skills;

• Ability to work on special projects and overtime hours as needed;

• Candidate must be experienced and comfortable driving a large vehicle throughout the five boroughs of New York City.

