Vision, Growth, and Operations
• Establish and maintain relationships with key business and technology stakeholders;
• Articulate and possess a strong interest in DoITT’s GIS products and the vision for improving the experience of New Yorkers while meeting key business objectives of stakeholders;
• Define the product roadmap based on business outcomes, defining which business capabilities the product should have, and what business outcomes those capabilities should achieve;
• Act as the “keeper (and communicator) of the vision” to translate the product strategy and vision developed with business stakeholders into what the product team must bear in mind every day to ensure they are building the right product;
• Collaborate closely on new projects and programs with Applications Division groups, any product delivery manager, and DevSecOps delivery teams charged with executing the roadmap. Work to sustain product teams to deliver and maintain the product;
• Manage the operational process of designing and running a product or service throughout its entire lifecycle. Plan and operationalize the stages of new product or service development by working closely with other operational delivery teams and DoITT leadership to guarantee that all relevant divisions are prepared to deliver and service the product continuously throughout its lifecycle. Plan for the retirement of products when they no longer meet user needs or are not in clear alignment with agency priorities and capabilities.

Customer Feedback
• In collaboration with DataOps and other City agency stakeholders, research to gain insight into the “voice of the customer,” analyze end-user feedback, determine how best to represent users throughout the delivery process, and how they would gain value from product capabilities;
• Work with key stakeholders to make frequent and dynamic prioritization decisions based on customer feedback;
