The Bureau of Law & Adjustment (BLA) settles and adjusts claims filed against and on behalf of the City of New York. After a claim is filed, it is investigated. Based on the results of the investigation, the Comptroller’s Office may extend an offer to settle the claim. If the claim cannot be settled, the claimant may choose to pursue the matter through the courts.

Reporting directly to the Director of Litigation, duties for the Legal Secretary position include, but are not limited to, the following:

- Provides direct administrative support to the Director, including but not limited to receiving incoming calls and messages; maintaining the Director’s schedule and calendar; and drafting correspondence on behalf of the Director;

- Manages the administrative and related office management activities of the Unit; maintains various office calendars and schedules meetings; maintains office files, including electronic files, performs data entry, and reviews, organize, and prioritize correspondence and claim materials received from external sources;

- Acts as a point of contact and liaison between the Director (and the Unit in general) and attorneys and claimants with respect to claim evaluation and resolution, including but not limited to scheduling settlement conferences, managing intake and closing documents, tracking and entering data into relevant spreadsheets, documents, and/or databases, and all other related tasks;

- Acts as a point of contact and liaison between the Director (and the Unit in general) and the New York City Law Department with respect to evaluation and analysis of in-litigation matters, including but not limited to reviewing litigation documents, prioritizing correspondence and requests for authority, monitoring and maintaining court appearance calendars, and all other related tasks;

- Liaises with other Divisions and Units within the Bureau as required to execute all Unit functions;
 
- Provides administrative support to the Deputy Director and other members of the Unit, and undertakes other general office support functions as needed;

- Maintains strict confidentiality of all matters under review by the Litigation Unit; and,

- Performs other related duties and assignments as may be required.

Preferred Skills:
- 1-3 years of litigation support or general legal administrative support experience, preferably civil litigation, in the areas of torts, personal injury, civil rights, medical malpractice, and/or employment litigation;

- Experience with electronic filing systems for both federal (PACER) and state (e-Courts) cases;

- Excellent interpersonal and organization skills;

- Detail oriented with excellent time management skills, ability to multi-task and prioritize assignments;

- Strong, collaborative work ethic;

- Proficient with full Microsoft Office Suite, including Outlook, Word, and Excel, video conferencing applications, and ability to gain expertise in various database programs as necessary.

Job Description:
NOTE: This position is open only to current City employees serving in a permanent civil service title of Clerical Associate.

Under the direction of the Timekeeping Supervisor, the Timekeeping Associate will serve as a Central Timekeeper and be responsible for the Timekeeping functions of the Comptroller’s Office 750 full-time and part-time employees.  Responsibilities include, but are not limited to, the following:

